WEBVTT

00:00:58.559 --> 00:00:59.393
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

00:00:59.477 --> 00:01:00.978
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY WITH SUPERVISION

00:01:02.855 --> 00:01:05.024
As we speak, it's a foul ball.

00:01:05.107 --> 00:01:06.692
The tension is high right now.

00:01:06.776 --> 00:01:08.736
The pitcher looks really shaken up.

00:01:08.819 --> 00:01:10.905
His breaking balls are in the middle of the zone.

00:01:13.783 --> 00:01:17.036
After getting into a jam with two outs, bases loaded in the bottom of the 9th,

00:01:17.119 --> 00:01:18.370
The pitcher's being pulled.

00:01:20.623 --> 00:01:22.374
And here comes Park Gi-yoon.

00:01:22.458 --> 00:01:24.251
SAEUM is putting their trust

00:01:24.335 --> 00:01:27.129
Into their veteran to get the final out.

00:01:27.213 --> 00:01:30.591
Park Gi-yoon steps onto the mound looking visibly flushed.

00:01:32.259 --> 00:01:33.844
The score is 5-2.

00:01:33.928 --> 00:01:37.807
SAEUM Sis only one out away from winning the Korean Series.

00:01:37.890 --> 00:01:41.852
But the question is, will they be able to get out of this crisis?

00:01:43.771 --> 00:01:46.190
The pitch bounces in the plate. Ball one.

00:01:46.273 --> 00:01:47.650
He's feeling the pressure.

00:01:47.733 --> 00:01:49.318
His body's way too tense right now.

00:01:49.401 --> 00:01:52.488
I warned you, you absolutely can't be late today!

00:01:52.571 --> 00:01:54.490
Did you get off the bus? Where are you?

00:01:54.573 --> 00:01:55.407
Ji-yoon.

00:01:55.491 --> 00:01:57.243
I'm going on a trip.

00:01:57.326 --> 00:01:59.870
Sorry, I know you said you had something to tell me.

00:01:59.954 --> 00:02:02.873
The ball goes over the left field wall!

00:02:02.957 --> 00:02:04.166
That's a home run!

00:02:04.250 --> 00:02:06.502
-A walk-off home run! -It went over the wall.

00:02:06.585 --> 00:02:08.170
-This is the worst. -Unbelievable!

00:02:08.254 --> 00:02:10.548
And that's how this ballgame ends!

00:02:10.631 --> 00:02:12.591
This is the stuff movies are made of.

00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:17.763
FINAL SAEUM (LOSS) 5 : 6 KP (WIN)

00:02:26.522 --> 00:02:27.857
JI-YOON & GA-EUL

00:02:48.878 --> 00:02:55.885
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

00:02:59.305 --> 00:03:01.015
Even when you get ghosted

00:03:03.267 --> 00:03:06.520
8 MONTHS LATER

00:03:07.563 --> 00:03:08.647
You still go to work.

00:03:18.365 --> 00:03:19.366
Even when you're unwell

00:03:24.413 --> 00:03:26.832
Even when your family passes away

00:03:39.553 --> 00:03:41.221
Even when you meet a complete dirtbag

00:03:48.312 --> 00:03:50.731
What, you want me to charge that for you too?

00:03:56.236 --> 00:03:57.154
You still go to work.

00:03:59.490 --> 00:04:01.659
SAFETY ALERT HEAVY RAIN WARNING IN EFFECT

00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:03.577
SAFETY ALERT HEAVY RAIN WARNING IN EFFECT

00:04:05.621 --> 00:04:06.538
DONGNIMMUN

00:04:06.622 --> 00:04:09.667
HEAVY RAIN WARNING IN EFFECT

00:04:13.212 --> 00:04:17.216
HEAVY RAIN WARNING IN EFFECT STAY INSIDE, SAFETY FIRST

00:04:28.352 --> 00:04:30.396
In this hellish work life,

00:04:31.021 --> 00:04:33.023
Will hope ever show itself?

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:24.658
Where are we going?

00:05:26.535 --> 00:05:27.369
To work.

00:05:27.953 --> 00:05:28.787
What?

00:05:39.923 --> 00:05:45.471
EPISODE 1 EVEN IF THE SKY FALLS, STILL CLOCKING IN!

00:05:56.106 --> 00:05:58.108
What heavy rain? It's perfectly sunny.

00:06:06.533 --> 00:06:07.785
Why did I come so early?

00:06:26.303 --> 00:06:27.971
Breaking! Three-No-Man is coming!

00:06:30.641 --> 00:06:32.684
Three-No-Man? Wasn't he over at the US office?

00:06:32.768 --> 00:06:35.646
Wow, my commute just got spicy for the first time in ages.

00:06:35.729 --> 00:06:38.524
Haha. Anyway, brace yourselves. I sense a bloodbath coming.

00:06:38.607 --> 00:06:40.692
"Three-No-Man"? Who are you talking about?

00:06:41.360 --> 00:06:43.070
-Geez, you're really out of the loop. -Hello.

00:06:43.153 --> 00:06:44.154
Hello.

00:06:45.364 --> 00:06:46.532
-Cha Ji-yoon. -You're here.

00:06:47.074 --> 00:06:48.992
I knew you'd come. Got these for a BOGO deal.

00:06:49.076 --> 00:06:51.495
Thanks. But don't you know Kang Si-woo?

00:06:52.204 --> 00:06:53.080
Kang Si-woo?

00:06:54.289 --> 00:06:56.041
Oh, that legendary workaholic?

00:06:56.125 --> 00:06:58.293
Exactly. That Kang Si-woo is Three-No-Man.

00:06:58.377 --> 00:06:59.461
I see.

00:06:59.545 --> 00:07:00.504
"I see"?

00:07:01.380 --> 00:07:02.422
No smile.

00:07:02.506 --> 00:07:03.799
No people.

00:07:03.882 --> 00:07:04.842
No sorry.

00:07:04.925 --> 00:07:06.176
This is Kang Si-woo.

00:07:06.260 --> 00:07:09.179
I requested those materials by today, but they're not in my inbox.

00:07:09.263 --> 00:07:10.639
Did my request get lost,

00:07:10.722 --> 00:07:13.016
Or are you simply a slow worker?

00:07:13.100 --> 00:07:14.935
The man with a cold face that never smiles.

00:07:15.018 --> 00:07:16.854
He rarely socializes with other people

00:07:16.937 --> 00:07:19.898
And never apologizes first, whether to those above or below him.

00:07:19.982 --> 00:07:22.484
We call him "Three-No-Man."

00:07:24.778 --> 00:07:25.988
Doors closing.

00:07:27.239 --> 00:07:30.033
Wait! Hang on!

00:07:30.117 --> 00:07:31.577
Oh, come on.

00:07:41.753 --> 00:07:42.671
This is Kang Si-woo.

00:07:42.754 --> 00:07:46.175
The man behind the legendary 100% task force project success rate!

00:07:46.258 --> 00:07:48.135
He was made manager after just five years

00:07:48.218 --> 00:07:49.803
After two special promotions!

00:07:49.887 --> 00:07:53.098
But behind Three-No-Man Kang Si-woo's success

00:07:53.182 --> 00:07:54.850
Lies the blood of countless people.

00:07:54.933 --> 00:07:56.268
I'll be back tomorrow.

00:07:56.977 --> 00:07:57.853
Yes.

00:08:01.857 --> 00:08:03.400
Have you been reading martial arts novels?

00:08:03.483 --> 00:08:06.445
Why would there be a bloodbath at an electronics company?

00:08:06.528 --> 00:08:08.447
When Mr. Kang's task forces are disbanded,

00:08:08.530 --> 00:08:11.200
The team members vanish without a trace. Didn't you know?

00:08:11.283 --> 00:08:12.326
What?

00:08:12.409 --> 00:08:13.994
Oh, man.

00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:16.663
I heard some even took leave to get therapy.

00:08:16.747 --> 00:08:18.123
Hey, No-ah.

00:08:22.628 --> 00:08:25.088
The group chat's been blowing up about Three-No-Man.

00:08:25.172 --> 00:08:26.215
I know.

00:08:26.298 --> 00:08:29.051
How big a deal is he that everyone's losing it before he's even here?

00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:30.636
Is he hot?

00:08:30.719 --> 00:08:32.387
Gosh, pay attention to office politics.

00:08:32.471 --> 00:08:33.972
Keep your eyes and ears open.

00:08:34.056 --> 00:08:36.350
There are 100,000 people at this company.

00:08:36.433 --> 00:08:39.770
How are you supposed to work if you stuff your head with every little rumor?

00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:42.439
Come on, what's wrong with you all?

00:08:43.482 --> 00:08:45.651
Why do you keep talking nonsense?

00:08:47.527 --> 00:08:50.697
What the heck are we supposed to do if you suspend the production?

00:08:53.158 --> 00:08:55.494
Hey. Launch is just around the corner.

00:08:55.577 --> 00:08:58.205
This is when we should be compromising and pulling together,

00:08:58.288 --> 00:08:59.122
But you're

00:09:00.123 --> 00:09:01.124
Huh?

00:09:02.334 --> 00:09:03.919
Then what about me?

00:09:04.002 --> 00:09:05.379
What am I supposed to do?

00:09:05.796 --> 00:09:06.713
Hello?

00:09:06.797 --> 00:09:07.631
Hel--

00:09:08.298 --> 00:09:09.132
Oh, this

00:09:12.344 --> 00:09:13.845
Is something wrong, sir?

00:09:13.929 --> 00:09:17.891
The researchers and the factory workers are at a standoff right now.

00:09:17.975 --> 00:09:19.977
The production line has stopped!

00:09:20.060 --> 00:09:21.687
What? Why?

00:09:21.770 --> 00:09:23.146
That's what I'd like to ask you.

00:09:23.981 --> 00:09:26.316
Just how did you people handle this work

00:09:26.400 --> 00:09:29.236
For things to blow up like this

00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:31.321
In the test production stage?

00:09:32.489 --> 00:09:33.991
Why are you standing there?

00:09:34.074 --> 00:09:36.451
Get down to the Gwangju factory right now!

00:09:36.535 --> 00:09:38.578
Ms. Cha, go to Gwangju.

00:09:39.162 --> 00:09:41.581
Get this under control and get the line back up.

00:09:42.165 --> 00:09:43.000
Me?

00:09:43.083 --> 00:09:44.626
You want me to go?

00:09:46.128 --> 00:09:47.587
If I leave now

00:09:50.048 --> 00:09:51.008
Three hours to get there,

00:09:51.091 --> 00:09:53.552
One hour for lunch, at least two hours to settle things,

00:09:53.635 --> 00:09:55.387
And three hours to get back. Nope.

00:09:56.221 --> 00:09:57.264
It'll be to late.

00:09:59.975 --> 00:10:03.103
People will scatter once it's lunchtime, so the situation will be over by then.

00:10:03.937 --> 00:10:05.272
Even if I head out now

00:10:05.814 --> 00:10:06.940
Okay then,

00:10:07.649 --> 00:10:08.734
Take the helicopter.

00:10:09.401 --> 00:10:12.779
Isn't the helicopter only for executives?

00:10:12.863 --> 00:10:15.324
Even regular employees can take it in an emergency.

00:10:16.450 --> 00:10:19.453
Hello, this is Product Planning Team 1 Manager Ko Young-sam.

00:10:19.536 --> 00:10:22.456
I'm requesting a helicopter to go to the Gwangju factory immediately.

00:10:29.296 --> 00:10:30.630
Is this really happening?

00:10:31.423 --> 00:10:32.674
Fine!

00:10:32.758 --> 00:10:35.302
I get to ride a helicopter and leave work on time.

00:10:35.385 --> 00:10:36.636
What a sweet deal.

00:10:37.012 --> 00:10:40.140
Huh? Oh, wow.

00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:42.434
Awesome.

00:10:46.146 --> 00:10:46.980
SAEUM GWANGJU FACTORY 1

00:10:47.064 --> 00:10:49.941
-We won't allow it! -We can't do it.

00:10:50.025 --> 00:10:51.234
We have standards at SAEUM.

00:10:51.318 --> 00:10:53.653
How can we put out ice like that and call it sphere ice?

00:10:54.529 --> 00:10:57.699
We did nothing more than produce it

00:10:57.783 --> 00:10:59.159
As designed by your team.

00:10:59.242 --> 00:11:00.869
It came out fine in the first test.

00:11:00.952 --> 00:11:03.330
What, did some sculptor carve the ice by hand back then?

00:11:03.413 --> 00:11:04.790
It comes out fine at first,

00:11:04.873 --> 00:11:06.625
But it ends up like that the more we produce.

00:11:06.708 --> 00:11:07.709
What do you expect us to do?

00:11:07.793 --> 00:11:08.627
Exactly.

00:11:08.710 --> 00:11:11.380
Then let's swap out the parts and reset the line again!

00:11:11.463 --> 00:11:13.799
For crying out loud. We tried everything already!

00:11:13.882 --> 00:11:15.801
No one else is complaining,

00:11:15.884 --> 00:11:19.429
So why the heck do you ice people keep going on like this?

00:11:20.889 --> 00:11:21.765
Look who's here.

00:11:22.682 --> 00:11:25.268
Oh, Ms. Cha from the Product Planning Team.

00:11:26.353 --> 00:11:27.187
Hi, Ms. Cha.

00:11:27.270 --> 00:11:29.106
Hi everyone, how are you all doing?

00:11:29.189 --> 00:11:30.107
Hello.

00:11:30.190 --> 00:11:31.608
-Hello. -You got here so fast.

00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:33.568
Oh my, look at poor Mr. Kim's face.

00:11:34.986 --> 00:11:37.322
Going back and forth between Seoul and Gwangju must've been a lot.

00:11:37.406 --> 00:11:39.116
I'm dying here.

00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:40.200
Here.

00:11:40.283 --> 00:11:41.952
This is arginine.

00:11:42.035 --> 00:11:43.870
They say it does wonders for fatigue.

00:11:44.788 --> 00:11:45.997
Make sure you take it, okay?

00:11:46.873 --> 00:11:49.000
Did you have a few drinks again last night?

00:11:49.084 --> 00:11:49.960
I went pretty hard.

00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:52.712
I tried all sorts of hangover remedies,

00:11:53.463 --> 00:11:54.840
And this one was the best.

00:11:55.590 --> 00:11:57.300
Just stick to this one, okay?

00:11:59.302 --> 00:12:00.762
The clarity really isn't great.

00:12:03.598 --> 00:12:05.475
But it's not like we can delay the launch.

00:12:07.060 --> 00:12:08.061
Wow, what is this?

00:12:08.854 --> 00:12:10.689
Is this some kind of magical orb?

00:12:11.690 --> 00:12:14.818
This in a highball would be absolutely amazing.

00:12:15.485 --> 00:12:16.361
See? She likes it.

00:12:16.445 --> 00:12:18.738
Well, obviously it's better than regular ice cubes.

00:12:18.822 --> 00:12:20.157
But see? It's not clear enough.

00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:22.117
But we can't make it any clearer than this!

00:12:22.200 --> 00:12:25.120
And that's why we should try changing the equipment!

00:12:25.203 --> 00:12:27.831
And how many times do I have to tell you? We can't!

00:12:28.623 --> 00:12:30.709
Okay, okay. In that case,

00:12:30.792 --> 00:12:33.462
How about we go ahead with test production right now

00:12:33.545 --> 00:12:37.674
And gradually improve it step by step?

00:12:37.757 --> 00:12:40.427
There are lots of other things we have to test anyway,

00:12:40.510 --> 00:12:43.805
Like the door opening and closing and the temperature changes.

00:12:44.473 --> 00:12:47.100
We have to make the launch no matter what, you know?

00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:48.935
Isn't that so?

00:12:49.019 --> 00:12:50.395
That's exactly what I mean.

00:12:52.105 --> 00:12:53.815
Why later and not now?

00:12:53.899 --> 00:12:55.150
What was that?

00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:07.621
I said, why would you improve it only after production?

00:13:15.587 --> 00:13:17.088
Because if we delay our launch,

00:13:17.172 --> 00:13:19.508
Our competitor could beat us to market.

00:13:19.633 --> 00:13:22.594
And what if that competitor makes higher quality ice than ours?

00:13:22.719 --> 00:13:24.888
We'd still have the first-mover advantage.

00:13:25.388 --> 00:13:28.350
We can't afford to fixate on development and lose on both fronts.

00:13:28.433 --> 00:13:31.186
Why not aim to win on both fronts from the start?

00:13:31.269 --> 00:13:33.063
I believe anticipating risks

00:13:33.772 --> 00:13:35.524
And thinking about the second-best option

00:13:35.607 --> 00:13:37.359
Is also an important part of the job.

00:13:41.029 --> 00:13:42.656
CHA JI-YOON, SR. ASSOCIATE

00:13:43.281 --> 00:13:44.491
"Sr. Associate Cha Ji-yoon."

00:13:45.951 --> 00:13:46.785
Yes?

00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:48.370
Is this how you work?

00:13:49.913 --> 00:13:51.414
What do you mean by that?

00:13:51.498 --> 00:13:54.584
A fallback is the last card you play after doing everything possible.

00:13:55.627 --> 00:13:57.379
Preparing a fallback in advance

00:13:58.380 --> 00:13:59.339
Is not a good attitude.

00:14:01.341 --> 00:14:02.926
I don't know who you are,

00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:06.846
But you're incredibly idealistic.

00:14:11.309 --> 00:14:12.435
I'm Kang Si-woo.

00:14:14.104 --> 00:14:15.438
Three-No-Man.

00:14:15.522 --> 00:14:16.565
Bloodbath.

00:14:17.148 --> 00:14:18.233
Blood.

00:14:23.405 --> 00:14:26.616
I heard you were coming back but didn't expect to see you here.

00:14:26.700 --> 00:14:29.160
There's nowhere better than the field to understand the work.

00:14:29.244 --> 00:14:30.745
I just stopped by before returning.

00:14:30.829 --> 00:14:32.831
I've heard a lot about you, Mr. Kang.

00:14:32.914 --> 00:14:35.083
It's almost lunch, why don't we eat together?

00:14:35.166 --> 00:14:37.752
No, thank you. I'll just look around a bit and leave.

00:14:49.806 --> 00:14:50.640
What do we do now?

00:14:51.266 --> 00:14:53.059
Why ask the obvious? We suspend production.

00:14:53.852 --> 00:14:54.769
Ice spikes!

00:14:56.688 --> 00:14:57.772
Ice spikes?

00:14:57.856 --> 00:14:59.065
You mean reverse icicles?

00:15:00.108 --> 00:15:02.986
Yes! Icicles are clear, aren't they?

00:15:03.069 --> 00:15:04.988
Maybe we could make it that way.

00:15:07.157 --> 00:15:08.908
That's adorable, Ms. Cha.

00:15:09.534 --> 00:15:10.619
Well,

00:15:10.702 --> 00:15:11.745
Work life is so bleak,

00:15:11.828 --> 00:15:14.497
At least it's nice that the Planning Team still has dreamers.

00:15:14.581 --> 00:15:15.915
We'll wrap things up here,

00:15:15.999 --> 00:15:17.792
You go focus on reporting back.

00:15:18.293 --> 00:15:20.879
MANAGER KO YOUNG-SAM

00:15:21.796 --> 00:15:23.965
Did word get there already?

00:15:25.091 --> 00:15:26.092
Man, I don't want to go back.

00:15:27.093 --> 00:15:27.927
I don't want to go.

00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:31.806
I'm sorry.

00:15:31.890 --> 00:15:34.184
Things got wrapped up faster than I expected.

00:15:34.267 --> 00:15:36.311
The sooner we go, the better. Let's go.

00:15:36.394 --> 00:15:37.312
Thank you.

00:15:43.693 --> 00:15:45.737
Hold on. I heard we have another passenger.

00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:47.530
-Another passenger? -Yes.

00:16:14.432 --> 00:16:15.975
I'd like to introduce myself properly.

00:16:16.518 --> 00:16:19.562
I'm Sr. Associate Cha Ji-yoon from Product Planning Team 1.

00:16:20.980 --> 00:16:23.775
I'm sorry I didn't recognize you earlier, Mr. Kang.

00:16:25.777 --> 00:16:26.736
You've changed a lot.

00:16:27.696 --> 00:16:28.530
Pardon?

00:16:34.786 --> 00:16:36.121
Weather radar check, clear.

00:16:37.038 --> 00:16:38.748
Is everything okay, Captain?

00:16:38.832 --> 00:16:40.375
Yes, everything's fine.

00:16:40.458 --> 00:16:43.962
It It's just that we got an emergency alert this morning.

00:16:44.045 --> 00:16:45.672
A heavy Heavy rain warning.

00:16:45.755 --> 00:16:48.591
It's still a while before it starts pouring down.

00:16:51.886 --> 00:16:55.557
You should check where your life vest is just in case.

00:16:55.640 --> 00:16:57.934
Are there any parachutes or something?

00:16:58.017 --> 00:16:59.018
Parachutes?

00:16:59.936 --> 00:17:01.604
You might start hyperventilating,

00:17:01.688 --> 00:17:03.606
So this Take this and

00:17:43.688 --> 00:17:44.981
I'll let you have this.

00:17:49.694 --> 00:17:51.070
Thank y

00:17:57.535 --> 00:18:00.830
I had you flown out in a helicopter to mediate,

00:18:01.998 --> 00:18:04.751
And you shut the whole thing down instead?

00:18:05.752 --> 00:18:07.045
What now?

00:18:08.129 --> 00:18:08.963
Huh?!

00:18:10.423 --> 00:18:11.466
I'm sorry, sir.

00:18:11.549 --> 00:18:12.550
I mean

00:18:13.676 --> 00:18:15.011
Am I the only one working here?

00:18:15.595 --> 00:18:17.764
Am I the only one getting paid?

00:18:21.017 --> 00:18:21.851
People,

00:18:22.477 --> 00:18:26.147
Come up with a way to contain this mess

00:18:26.231 --> 00:18:28.566
And report back by tomorrow morning.

00:18:29.984 --> 00:18:31.569
-Got it? -Yes, sir.

00:18:32.111 --> 00:18:32.946
Geez.

00:18:34.906 --> 00:18:35.740
Ugh!

00:18:42.539 --> 00:18:44.374
Always acting like he's the only one who works.

00:18:48.878 --> 00:18:50.213
Are you okay, Ms. Cha?

00:18:50.797 --> 00:18:51.673
Of course, I'm okay.

00:18:53.550 --> 00:18:54.509
This isn't anything new.

00:18:55.593 --> 00:18:57.929
Let's hurry and go figure out a solution.

00:19:05.520 --> 00:19:07.897
RESPONSE PLAN FOR THE SPHERE ICE REFRIGERATOR SUSPENSION

00:19:22.495 --> 00:19:24.289
SPHERE ICE REFRIGERATOR RESPONSE PLAN FINAL FOR REAL

00:19:25.290 --> 00:19:26.416
Time to clock out!

00:19:27.166 --> 00:19:28.668
Time to clock out!

00:19:28.751 --> 00:19:30.211
Time to clock out!

00:19:35.383 --> 00:19:38.011
All right, I'm off.

00:19:41.014 --> 00:19:42.181
Of course, Clock-out Fairy.

00:19:42.765 --> 00:19:44.267
Did you finish the report?

00:19:44.350 --> 00:19:47.270
It's pouring outside, so don't forget your umbrellas.

00:19:56.070 --> 00:19:58.156
Where does Ms. Cha always go

00:19:58.239 --> 00:20:00.533
When she leaves right on time like that every day?

00:20:00.617 --> 00:20:01.743
Does she go to the gym?

00:20:01.826 --> 00:20:03.369
-Come on. -Come on.

00:20:03.453 --> 00:20:05.330
-Then is it for a date? -Come on!

00:20:35.109 --> 00:20:36.069
That's the stuff.

00:20:39.364 --> 00:20:40.198
Hey Buddy,

00:20:40.949 --> 00:20:43.868
Play some music for an exhausted office worker.

00:20:43.952 --> 00:20:48.247
Way back home, way back home

00:20:48.331 --> 00:20:52.126
I'm the happiest when I clock out

00:20:52.210 --> 00:20:55.254
Oh beautiful, so beautiful

00:20:55.338 --> 00:20:56.297
TURN OFF NOTIFICATIONS

00:20:56.381 --> 00:20:57.423
SAEUM 1919

00:20:57.507 --> 00:20:58.591
TURN OFF NOTIFICATIONS

00:20:59.175 --> 00:21:00.385
Off.

00:21:01.135 --> 00:21:02.095
Off.

00:21:08.267 --> 00:21:10.103
Is this how you work?

00:21:10.186 --> 00:21:13.231
A fallback is the last card you play after doing everything possible.

00:21:14.190 --> 00:21:16.109
Preparing a fallback in advance

00:21:17.026 --> 00:21:18.277
Is not a good attitude.

00:21:18.361 --> 00:21:19.988
What do you want?

00:21:20.071 --> 00:21:21.739
That was the best option for me.

00:21:29.330 --> 00:21:31.374
Another day of wanting to quit.

00:21:39.507 --> 00:21:40.717
RESIGNATION URGE STICKERS

00:21:45.430 --> 00:21:46.848
[SAEUM CARD] PAYMENT DUE: JULY 15

00:21:48.391 --> 00:21:49.684
AMOUNT DUE: 1,829,890 WON

00:21:56.024 --> 00:21:57.066
I can't quit.

00:22:00.194 --> 00:22:01.237
Ugh, never mind!

00:22:01.612 --> 00:22:02.447
I'm not quitting.

00:22:07.910 --> 00:22:08.745
It's here.

00:22:14.083 --> 00:22:15.877
It's not like I don't know what the best option is.

00:22:15.960 --> 00:22:18.713
You look for the second best because the best doesn't work.

00:22:19.630 --> 00:22:22.258
Hey, but still, throwing up

00:22:23.009 --> 00:22:24.052
Was a bit too much.

00:22:25.386 --> 00:22:26.804
Whatever.

00:22:26.888 --> 00:22:28.931
Why did he have to ride the helicopter with me?

00:22:29.682 --> 00:22:31.267
That's why they say

00:22:32.018 --> 00:22:33.770
You meet your nemesis at work.

00:22:33.853 --> 00:22:35.980
Just stay out of his sight and avoid him.

00:22:37.023 --> 00:22:39.025
Our company is so huge,

00:22:39.108 --> 00:22:42.570
So what are the chances of me running into a big shot like him again?

00:22:42.653 --> 00:22:44.697
Is that why you're having chicken and beer already?

00:22:44.781 --> 00:22:45.740
Hey.

00:22:46.365 --> 00:22:49.202
These are the only things that keep me going.

00:22:49.285 --> 00:22:51.954
Hye-ji, now that you're a mom, how else am I supposed to blow off steam?

00:22:57.293 --> 00:22:58.961
I mean, this looks doable.

00:22:59.879 --> 00:23:01.005
Why did they say it's not?

00:23:02.507 --> 00:23:03.800
Huh? What?

00:23:04.509 --> 00:23:05.593
Just something.

00:23:06.135 --> 00:23:09.138
Wait, you're not still pining over Ga-eul, are you?

00:23:09.222 --> 00:23:11.182
Why are you bringing up that name?

00:23:11.265 --> 00:23:12.975
You scared me. Why are you getting so worked up?

00:23:15.394 --> 00:23:17.730
Great, now you woke Seo-jun. I'm hanging up.

00:23:29.742 --> 00:23:32.745
STANDING EGG - OLD SONG

00:23:40.878 --> 00:23:42.004
I hate love.

00:23:44.382 --> 00:23:47.051
YEAR 2013

00:23:48.010 --> 00:23:50.972
I take another look

00:23:51.055 --> 00:23:54.642
Wondering if it's you

00:23:54.725 --> 00:23:57.395
I keep turning back

00:23:57.478 --> 00:24:00.481
Hoping it's you

00:24:01.440 --> 00:24:04.318
Somewhere

00:24:04.402 --> 00:24:07.363
Are you listening to the same song?

00:24:08.072 --> 00:24:11.284
Could you be standing still too

00:24:11.367 --> 00:24:14.120
Thinking of me?

00:24:22.044 --> 00:24:22.879
Hi.

00:24:23.838 --> 00:24:24.672
Hello.

00:24:27.216 --> 00:24:28.801
You're a very good singer.

00:24:34.849 --> 00:24:36.475
What instrument do you play?

00:24:36.559 --> 00:24:37.351
Sorry?

00:24:44.066 --> 00:24:45.026
Drum

00:24:48.571 --> 00:24:49.655
That's so cool.

00:24:51.741 --> 00:24:52.575
Here.

00:24:53.701 --> 00:24:58.664
"COSMOS" BAND SIGN-UP FORM

00:25:01.000 --> 00:25:01.834
Welcome.

00:25:10.343 --> 00:25:11.969
The way it gives you

00:25:12.762 --> 00:25:15.056
A strange kind of courage you've never had before.

00:25:27.860 --> 00:25:30.613
Just like the song

00:25:30.696 --> 00:25:34.033
We used to share a long time ago

00:25:34.116 --> 00:25:37.620
That drifted toward me

00:25:37.703 --> 00:25:40.706
On the street by chance

00:25:46.504 --> 00:25:47.880
The way a brief smile

00:25:47.964 --> 00:25:50.508
Makes you dream of a bond that lasts forever.

00:26:02.561 --> 00:26:04.063
I'm enlisting next week.

00:26:06.148 --> 00:26:07.149
What?

00:26:07.817 --> 00:26:08.651
Buy me a meal when I'm out.

00:26:13.114 --> 00:26:15.866
The way you don't get tired of waiting for an answer that never comes.

00:26:15.950 --> 00:26:19.328
To Ga-eul's final military leave!

00:26:19.412 --> 00:26:20.579
Cheers.

00:26:22.039 --> 00:26:23.624
Will you come back to school as soon as you're out?

00:26:24.292 --> 00:26:25.251
I'm going to Australia.

00:26:25.334 --> 00:26:28.004
I'm going to make music in the great outdoors all I want.

00:26:32.466 --> 00:26:33.342
That's so cool.

00:26:35.845 --> 00:26:37.221
That'll be 10,300 won.

00:26:37.305 --> 00:26:41.809
YEAR 2021

00:26:42.893 --> 00:26:43.728
These too, please.

00:26:47.189 --> 00:26:48.024
Hi.

00:26:48.607 --> 00:26:49.483
Ga-eul!

00:26:50.401 --> 00:26:51.360
How have you been?

00:26:52.737 --> 00:26:56.282
What made me believe every one of those moments was fate

00:26:56.365 --> 00:26:57.199
Was love.

00:27:02.413 --> 00:27:03.581
I hate love.

00:27:05.291 --> 00:27:06.584
It makes too many things

00:27:07.418 --> 00:27:08.586
Seem possible.

00:27:21.307 --> 00:27:22.141
Next.

00:27:22.516 --> 00:27:23.684
JEON KEE-TAE PRODUCT PLANNING TEAM 2

00:27:29.732 --> 00:27:30.608
Next.

00:27:31.233 --> 00:27:33.277
PARK MI-YOUNG PRODUCT PLANNING TEAM 2

00:27:46.665 --> 00:27:49.418
CHA JI-YOON PRODUCT PLANNING TEAM 1

00:27:49.502 --> 00:27:52.880
CHA JI-YOON SR. ASSOCIATE

00:28:03.766 --> 00:28:06.227
I'm Manager Kang Si-woo, the new team lead

00:28:06.310 --> 00:28:07.645
For Product Planning Team 2.

00:28:09.688 --> 00:28:11.899
Why does he have to be on the team next to mine?

00:28:16.320 --> 00:28:17.613
What happened to our team lead?

00:28:17.696 --> 00:28:19.865
He's currently on leave due to health issues.

00:28:20.533 --> 00:28:21.909
That came out of nowhere.

00:28:21.992 --> 00:28:23.077
He was fine, wasn't he?

00:28:23.160 --> 00:28:23.994
I know, right?

00:28:24.078 --> 00:28:25.579
Did he have a medical condition?

00:28:25.663 --> 00:28:27.081
Let me introduce myself.

00:28:27.164 --> 00:28:28.874
I'm Associate Jeon Kee-tae.

00:28:29.667 --> 00:28:31.127
Jeon is my last name.

00:28:31.585 --> 00:28:32.420
Okay.

00:28:33.462 --> 00:28:36.507
Associates Park Mi-young, Kim Yeong-jin, Han Jae-rim, Kim Seung-ji,

00:28:36.590 --> 00:28:37.883
And Jeon Kee-tae.

00:28:37.967 --> 00:28:39.677
Sr. Associates Choi Jung-in, Park In-cheol.

00:28:39.760 --> 00:28:42.513
I know all of your names and titles, so no need to tell me.

00:28:43.764 --> 00:28:46.142
I'll be communicating with you via messages from now on.

00:28:47.268 --> 00:28:49.145
Report your work to me by email.

00:28:49.228 --> 00:28:52.898
Now, please start by putting together a list of your current tasks

00:28:52.982 --> 00:28:54.150
And sending it to me.

00:28:56.318 --> 00:28:59.905
Should we all go out for lunch as a welcome meal

00:28:59.989 --> 00:29:01.991
For you, Mr. Kang?

00:29:02.074 --> 00:29:05.119
I'll eat on my own after checking your emails.

00:29:05.202 --> 00:29:06.328
All right, then.

00:29:15.129 --> 00:29:16.213
Good luck.

00:29:30.186 --> 00:29:32.813
That means he wants everyone to finish before lunch, right?

00:29:32.897 --> 00:29:34.315
It means they shouldn't even

00:29:34.398 --> 00:29:36.734
Think about having lunch unless they finish.

00:29:37.943 --> 00:29:40.279
You think Mr. Ko is better compared to Three-No-Man?

00:29:40.362 --> 00:29:42.156
You mean, choose who's the worst

00:29:42.781 --> 00:29:43.741
And the second worst?

00:29:46.118 --> 00:29:47.328
Mr. Ko's coming.

00:29:57.755 --> 00:29:59.840
In and out, and in and out.

00:29:59.924 --> 00:30:02.551
What is this, an office or a temple?

00:30:03.802 --> 00:30:05.804
Let me look at your reports.

00:30:11.644 --> 00:30:12.603
RESPONSE PLAN

00:30:16.607 --> 00:30:19.777
You've been a Sr. Associate for that long, and you bring me this?

00:30:19.860 --> 00:30:21.403
You want to be a Sr. Associate forever?

00:30:22.112 --> 00:30:22.988
I'm sorry, sir.

00:30:26.158 --> 00:30:28.619
That new team lead won't give you advice like this.

00:30:28.702 --> 00:30:30.371
He'll be busy looking out for himself

00:30:30.454 --> 00:30:32.706
No matter what happens to his people.

00:30:42.174 --> 00:30:43.300
Thank you.

00:30:44.510 --> 00:30:46.637
I wish I could tell myself from five years ago

00:30:46.720 --> 00:30:48.806
To write your cover letter and run somewhere else.

00:30:51.350 --> 00:30:53.978
I wish I could tell myself from when I was your age to learn

00:30:54.061 --> 00:30:55.396
From someone who's smart and competent,

00:30:55.479 --> 00:30:58.691
Instead of working under a boss who just dumps work on you

00:30:58.774 --> 00:31:00.859
While sucking up to the higher-ups.

00:31:01.360 --> 00:31:03.195
You can do that now, can't you?

00:31:03.279 --> 00:31:04.154
It's too late for me.

00:31:04.238 --> 00:31:07.199
I'm already used to a boss who only does the bare minimum.

00:31:08.117 --> 00:31:10.077
Is this the so-called seven-year slump?

00:31:12.955 --> 00:31:14.832
LADY NAM

00:31:15.791 --> 00:31:16.625
Hey, Mom.

00:31:16.709 --> 00:31:17.876
You haven't eaten yet, right?

00:31:18.877 --> 00:31:20.004
I was just about to eat.

00:31:20.087 --> 00:31:21.630
I'm by your office, so just come out.

00:31:21.714 --> 00:31:22.840
I'll send you directions.

00:31:22.923 --> 00:31:24.049
Mom.

00:31:24.133 --> 00:31:25.050
Mom?

00:31:38.188 --> 00:31:40.065
SLOW POKE

00:31:50.576 --> 00:31:51.660
Ms. Cha Ji-yoon?

00:31:53.370 --> 00:31:54.246
That's me.

00:31:55.164 --> 00:31:56.248
And you are?

00:31:56.957 --> 00:31:58.083
Hello.

00:31:58.167 --> 00:32:00.544
I'm Lee Jeong-woo. I'm here to meet you.

00:32:01.170 --> 00:32:02.004
Pardon?

00:32:07.343 --> 00:32:08.636
Just a moment, please.

00:32:22.691 --> 00:32:24.068
Come on, pick up.

00:32:38.207 --> 00:32:39.375
Can I go in?

00:33:02.314 --> 00:33:05.609
If your fridge or washing machine breaks, do you fix them yourself?

00:33:07.069 --> 00:33:08.195
No, I call for service.

00:33:08.821 --> 00:33:10.155
What about computers?

00:33:10.239 --> 00:33:13.367
My friends who were engineering majors usually build their own.

00:33:14.576 --> 00:33:16.161
There are good all-in-ones these days.

00:33:18.163 --> 00:33:20.666
Still, it's pretty incredible that you work

00:33:20.749 --> 00:33:22.084
At an electronics company.

00:33:23.043 --> 00:33:24.545
My mom totally freaks out

00:33:24.628 --> 00:33:26.547
When the circuit breaker trips.

00:33:27.423 --> 00:33:28.799
My sister once called someone

00:33:29.383 --> 00:33:31.301
Just because a light bulb went out

00:33:33.387 --> 00:33:35.305
And got into a huge fight with her husband.

00:33:35.931 --> 00:33:38.225
Running into someone from work is bad enough,

00:33:39.143 --> 00:33:40.936
So why did it have to be Three-No-Man?

00:33:41.562 --> 00:33:42.771
Oh, Ji-yoon,

00:33:43.397 --> 00:33:44.898
You've got some sauce on your face.

00:33:46.442 --> 00:33:47.985
No, the other side.

00:34:10.048 --> 00:34:12.718
I should tell you before this gets any more awkward.

00:34:12.801 --> 00:34:13.969
Tell me what?

00:34:14.052 --> 00:34:17.431
I'm in a temporary no-dating phase.

00:34:20.058 --> 00:34:20.893
Oh, right.

00:34:22.311 --> 00:34:25.063
I haven't completely ended things

00:34:25.689 --> 00:34:27.900
With my ex-boyfriend yet.

00:34:30.360 --> 00:34:31.695
I'm so sorry

00:34:32.529 --> 00:34:34.323
For wasting your time like this.

00:34:37.201 --> 00:34:38.535
So

00:34:40.704 --> 00:34:41.663
I'll pay

00:34:43.582 --> 00:34:44.833
For your lunch.

00:34:47.795 --> 00:34:49.421
This caller is unavailable.

00:34:49.505 --> 00:34:50.589
Not answering, huh?

00:34:51.965 --> 00:34:53.801
I swear, I'm going to disown her.

00:34:56.345 --> 00:34:57.429
Hey, Ms. Choi!

00:34:58.055 --> 00:35:00.015
Ji-yoon! Have you been well?

00:35:00.098 --> 00:35:00.933
Yes.

00:35:01.517 --> 00:35:02.935
I saw you won the Design of the Year award.

00:35:03.018 --> 00:35:04.144
Congratulations.

00:35:04.228 --> 00:35:05.145
Thank you.

00:35:07.648 --> 00:35:10.025
Would you like to come for some food, if you have time?

00:35:12.319 --> 00:35:13.153
Are you perhaps

00:35:13.237 --> 00:35:14.863
She's getting married.

00:35:15.489 --> 00:35:17.991
Congratulations! Of course, I'll be at your wedding.

00:35:18.075 --> 00:35:19.117
No pressure, though.

00:35:19.785 --> 00:35:21.620
-Okay. -See you later.

00:35:21.703 --> 00:35:22.996
Shall we head out?

00:35:23.080 --> 00:35:24.498
-Bye! -Take care.

00:35:26.333 --> 00:35:28.001
I'm so jealous of the Design Team

00:35:28.085 --> 00:35:30.295
That they get to work with a cool boss like her.

00:35:30.379 --> 00:35:31.213
Tell me about it.

00:35:31.296 --> 00:35:34.007
She's talented, straightforward, and funny.

00:35:34.508 --> 00:35:37.427
She's my greatest mentor and role model.

00:35:40.097 --> 00:35:41.682
I need to book a wedding venue too.

00:35:42.766 --> 00:35:43.934
I hear your boyfriend is very sweet.

00:35:44.560 --> 00:35:45.769
I'm so jealous!

00:35:45.853 --> 00:35:46.687
Sorry?

00:35:50.023 --> 00:35:52.651
Boyfriend? What is she on about?

00:35:52.776 --> 00:35:53.735
Ms. Cha.

00:35:55.153 --> 00:35:57.322
-I heard you're getting married soon. -No, I'm not.

00:35:57.406 --> 00:35:59.700
Come on, don't be so shy.

00:35:59.783 --> 00:36:00.826
Congratulations.

00:36:01.368 --> 00:36:02.327
Wait.

00:36:04.329 --> 00:36:06.081
Ms. Cha, what's happening?

00:36:06.164 --> 00:36:07.666
I don't know.

00:36:08.917 --> 00:36:10.085
Maybe there's a fake rumor.

00:36:12.754 --> 00:36:16.091
Well, well. I heard lunch blind dates are all the rage these days,

00:36:16.174 --> 00:36:18.385
But I had no idea our dear colleague was this trendy.

00:36:18.468 --> 00:36:20.721
Was it sparks at first sight, all fireworks?

00:36:21.471 --> 00:36:23.223
Did you just come back from a blind date?

00:36:23.307 --> 00:36:24.975
-No-ah, go on in first. -Wait!

00:36:25.058 --> 00:36:26.018
-Quiet. -Why?

00:36:26.602 --> 00:36:27.936
-Isn't it true? -Wait, a blind date

00:36:28.478 --> 00:36:29.354
Don't go, No-ah.

00:36:31.773 --> 00:36:33.901
What the hell? Who said I went on a blind date?

00:36:33.984 --> 00:36:35.444
I saw it on the online forum.

00:36:35.527 --> 00:36:38.739
Here. See? The forum's blowing up right now.

00:36:42.200 --> 00:36:44.745
Looks like Planning Team 1's Sr. Associate "C" will get married soon.

00:36:44.828 --> 00:36:47.706
Heard someone saw her on a blind date at a poke place during lunch.

00:36:47.789 --> 00:36:49.917
The man stroked her face and everything.

00:36:50.000 --> 00:36:51.209
-Wait. -Really?

00:36:51.293 --> 00:36:53.587
So, the Clock-out Fairy doesn't even waste lunchtime.

00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:54.671
Is she a Blind-Date Fairy now?

00:36:54.755 --> 00:36:56.465
-Hahaha. -Wonder if it went well.

00:36:58.300 --> 00:36:59.134
Hang on.

00:37:05.307 --> 00:37:06.183
"Hang on"?

00:37:17.778 --> 00:37:19.863
Hey, is it fake news?

00:37:21.323 --> 00:37:22.157
Is it raining?

00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:25.035
He spread a rumor in that short amount of time?

00:37:25.994 --> 00:37:27.496
I didn't think he'd do such a thing.

00:37:27.996 --> 00:37:29.873
Who did the "No People" Three-No-Man even tell?

00:37:31.124 --> 00:37:33.418
But he's the only one who saw the guy touch my face.

00:37:46.056 --> 00:37:47.474
Did you enjoy your lunch?

00:37:48.183 --> 00:37:49.059
Yes.

00:37:55.399 --> 00:37:56.358
By any chance,

00:37:57.150 --> 00:37:59.194
Did you hear the rumor

00:37:59.820 --> 00:38:01.405
That I was on a blind date at lunch?

00:38:02.197 --> 00:38:03.490
Was that a blind date?

00:38:04.074 --> 00:38:07.160
I went on the date against my will, but I won't ever see him again.

00:38:07.244 --> 00:38:08.870
Why would someone spread

00:38:08.954 --> 00:38:12.207
A rumor like that when they don't know the full story?

00:38:13.625 --> 00:38:15.293
You expect me to know the answer?

00:38:16.503 --> 00:38:17.462
It wasn't him.

00:38:18.547 --> 00:38:20.507
There's a lot of fake news around the office.

00:38:21.216 --> 00:38:22.342
Just letting you know.

00:38:29.057 --> 00:38:30.684
JULY 26 PARK HYEONG-JIN AND CHOI SOO-JIN

00:38:31.852 --> 00:38:35.063
Manager Choi Soo-jin from the Design Team is getting married.

00:38:35.147 --> 00:38:36.815
Are you going to the wedding?

00:38:43.989 --> 00:38:45.824
Don't you think you should go?

00:38:45.907 --> 00:38:49.745
The Planning Team and Design Team work together a lot.

00:38:52.414 --> 00:38:53.915
Why would I go there?

00:39:04.926 --> 00:39:07.137
What's his problem?

00:39:14.102 --> 00:39:16.813
Why would you send a man right where my office is?

00:39:16.897 --> 00:39:19.357
Do you know what kind of humiliation I went through?

00:39:19.441 --> 00:39:21.610
I wouldn't have done it if you were doing well yourself.

00:39:21.693 --> 00:39:23.236
What am I not doing well?

00:39:23.320 --> 00:39:25.280
Why ask the obvious? Getting married.

00:39:25.864 --> 00:39:28.700
Who even gets married at my age these days?

00:39:28.784 --> 00:39:31.703
If you weren't going to marry, why did you live with--

00:39:32.329 --> 00:39:33.538
Live with?

00:39:33.622 --> 00:39:34.998
What are you on about?

00:39:35.082 --> 00:39:36.792
I didn't say anything!

00:39:38.794 --> 00:39:39.669
You brat.

00:39:40.253 --> 00:39:42.214
You give back every cent I sent you.

00:39:43.590 --> 00:39:44.508
Fine.

00:39:45.175 --> 00:39:47.385
I never saw it myself and you were never caught,

00:39:47.469 --> 00:39:49.429
So that means nothing happened, right?

00:39:50.013 --> 00:39:51.848
It did happen. What do you mean nothing happened?

00:39:51.932 --> 00:39:54.601
Yes, I lived with Ga-eul

00:39:54.684 --> 00:39:57.104
And even thought about getting married, but we broke up. So what?

00:39:57.187 --> 00:40:00.690
Exactly, so now go meet a decent guy and get married already!

00:40:00.774 --> 00:40:01.650
No!

00:40:02.234 --> 00:40:03.777
Seriously.

00:40:07.072 --> 00:40:07.906
Did you

00:40:09.407 --> 00:40:11.159
Take money from your sister too?

00:40:11.243 --> 00:40:13.036
I was just trying to be a peacekeeper.

00:40:13.120 --> 00:40:14.037
You little!

00:40:14.121 --> 00:40:16.957
I can forgive cohabitation, but I won't forgive two-timing, you punk!

00:40:19.126 --> 00:40:20.418
I'm home.

00:40:20.502 --> 00:40:21.795
The hamburger?

00:40:24.005 --> 00:40:25.048
Here.

00:40:26.758 --> 00:40:28.552
Stop eating junk like this.

00:40:36.476 --> 00:40:37.477
Did you pull an all-nighter?

00:40:38.728 --> 00:40:39.688
Yeah.

00:40:40.939 --> 00:40:43.358
So why would you quit your job

00:40:43.441 --> 00:40:45.026
To write some web novel?

00:40:45.110 --> 00:40:46.736
If you want to, write a fantasy novel.

00:40:47.320 --> 00:40:48.613
Office Proposal?

00:40:49.156 --> 00:40:50.866
Who would read about coworkers dating?

00:40:51.491 --> 00:40:53.994
Why are you nagging me again the second you walk in?

00:40:54.077 --> 00:40:57.205
You need to get it together and start dating again and all that.

00:40:59.082 --> 00:41:01.626
So why date a jerk like that just to break off your engagement?

00:41:11.344 --> 00:41:12.470
GOO-WON

00:41:12.554 --> 00:41:13.889
Babe, did you have dinner?

00:41:13.972 --> 00:41:15.807
Where should we go this weekend?

00:41:17.017 --> 00:41:18.351
I guess he's swamped.

00:41:22.355 --> 00:41:24.191
I just sent you an email,

00:41:24.274 --> 00:41:26.276
So pull up the response plan from the attachment.

00:41:27.861 --> 00:41:28.945
This last minute?

00:41:32.991 --> 00:41:35.911
I heard even the test production stopped because of this clarity issue.

00:41:35.994 --> 00:41:36.828
So, Mr. Ko,

00:41:36.912 --> 00:41:39.956
What will happen if this situation drags on?

00:41:40.040 --> 00:41:42.542
That's why I've prepared a response plan.

00:41:44.211 --> 00:41:45.212
Ms. Cha.

00:41:45.295 --> 00:41:46.338
Yes.

00:41:51.218 --> 00:41:53.220
I propose we launch in North America first

00:41:53.887 --> 00:41:56.556
If the domestic launch gets stalled.

00:41:56.640 --> 00:41:59.351
Wait. This is mine.

00:42:01.811 --> 00:42:04.397
None of these are good enough.

00:42:06.358 --> 00:42:08.235
I'll handle this report myself.

00:42:08.318 --> 00:42:10.028
Send all your reports to me by email.

00:42:10.111 --> 00:42:11.029
NORTH AMERICAN MARKET SURVEY ON SPHERE ICE

00:42:11.112 --> 00:42:12.113
Yes, sir.

00:42:13.490 --> 00:42:17.911
Our market research shows that demand for sphere ice is higher in North America

00:42:17.994 --> 00:42:19.454
Than the domestic market,

00:42:19.537 --> 00:42:24.209
So the consumers there care more about the shape and function than clarity.

00:42:24.292 --> 00:42:25.543
So,

00:42:25.627 --> 00:42:28.046
We should target overseas markets first,

00:42:28.129 --> 00:42:31.007
Then use that success to build momentum for the domestic laun--

00:42:32.133 --> 00:42:33.343
404 NOT FOUND

00:42:38.598 --> 00:42:39.808
Well, uh

00:42:39.891 --> 00:42:42.602
Domestic launch

00:42:43.436 --> 00:42:44.813
What are you doing, Ms. Cha?

00:42:44.896 --> 00:42:45.939
I apologize.

00:42:46.022 --> 00:42:47.941
There's been an error. Let me reboot it.

00:42:50.402 --> 00:42:52.779
Mr. Ko. Please continue.

00:42:52.862 --> 00:42:54.155
Right. Of course.

00:42:54.239 --> 00:42:57.450
Well, if we launch overseas I mean in North America,

00:42:57.534 --> 00:42:59.619
We'll break into that market, and then

00:43:01.830 --> 00:43:04.749
I think it'd be better for me to explain with some visual aid.

00:43:04.833 --> 00:43:07.043
Then let me ask you a question in the meantime.

00:43:08.837 --> 00:43:09.671
Sure.

00:43:09.754 --> 00:43:11.131
What is sphere ice?

00:43:13.174 --> 00:43:15.010
You just came from the US.

00:43:15.760 --> 00:43:18.263
Haven't you been to a whiskey bar, Mr. Kang?

00:43:18.346 --> 00:43:21.433
Sphere ice is an ice ball shaped like an orb.

00:43:21.516 --> 00:43:22.392
No, not that.

00:43:23.184 --> 00:43:26.146
I'm asking you about its qualities, not its shape.

00:43:26.229 --> 00:43:28.440
It melts more slowly than regular ice cubes,

00:43:28.523 --> 00:43:32.694
So it lets you enjoy the drink's original flavor for longer.

00:43:33.320 --> 00:43:36.281
Couldn't you just use an ice mold already on the market for that?

00:43:36.364 --> 00:43:39.534
A sphere-ice refrigerator is more costly than a regular one.

00:43:40.243 --> 00:43:41.244
Why should one buy it then?

00:43:42.829 --> 00:43:44.122
Well

00:43:44.205 --> 00:43:45.206
In that case,

00:43:45.290 --> 00:43:48.752
What do you think is the core value of sphere ice, Mr. Kang?

00:43:49.377 --> 00:43:50.587
Its aesthetics.

00:43:52.297 --> 00:43:54.549
People pay more to buy luxury bags

00:43:54.632 --> 00:43:57.552
Not because of function, but because of their rarity and design.

00:43:58.053 --> 00:44:00.764
The sphere ice our refrigerator makes has to be like that.

00:44:00.847 --> 00:44:03.183
Not some rough imitation of an ice chunk,

00:44:03.266 --> 00:44:07.479
But a clear and perfect luxury product made possible by innovative technology.

00:44:07.562 --> 00:44:09.856
As I explained earlier,

00:44:09.939 --> 00:44:11.816
That's not possible with current technology, so

00:44:11.900 --> 00:44:13.526
Do you think so too, Ms. Cha?

00:44:14.319 --> 00:44:15.278
Pardon?

00:44:15.362 --> 00:44:18.281
Is there really no other way to make the ice clearer?

00:44:23.828 --> 00:44:25.038
Ice spikes!

00:44:25.747 --> 00:44:27.374
Icicles are clear, aren’t they?

00:44:27.999 --> 00:44:29.751
Maybe we could make it that way.

00:44:41.054 --> 00:44:42.055
There isn't.

00:44:45.683 --> 00:44:46.851
So then,

00:44:46.935 --> 00:44:49.396
What's your verdict, Mr. Kang?

00:44:49.479 --> 00:44:51.648
The sphere ice refrigerator launch plan

00:44:52.232 --> 00:44:53.817
Should be suspended entirely.

00:44:59.656 --> 00:45:01.324
We've already come this far.

00:45:01.408 --> 00:45:04.244
Stopping so suddenly seems just

00:45:05.370 --> 00:45:08.581
If we stop now, we'll have to absorb enormous losses.

00:45:09.374 --> 00:45:11.209
That's an irresponsible thing to say.

00:45:11.292 --> 00:45:14.838
The losses will be less than the cost of launching a flawed product.

00:45:30.437 --> 00:45:33.565
Stealing your own subordinate's report?

00:45:33.648 --> 00:45:35.692
Way to hit a new low, you shameless boss!

00:45:38.736 --> 00:45:39.571
You know what?

00:45:39.654 --> 00:45:41.781
If the pay's the same,

00:45:41.865 --> 00:45:43.741
Better a salary thief than a corporate slave.

00:45:45.118 --> 00:45:46.619
I'll do just that.

00:45:47.287 --> 00:45:49.247
Is this the model that was presented at CES?

00:45:49.330 --> 00:45:51.040
CES: A GLOBAL ELECTRONICS TRADE SHOW FOR UNVEILING NEW PRODUCTS

00:45:51.124 --> 00:45:51.958
Yes.

00:45:53.585 --> 00:45:54.919
Why didn't you tell them?

00:45:56.171 --> 00:45:57.005
Sorry?

00:45:57.297 --> 00:45:58.381
About ice spikes.

00:46:01.301 --> 00:46:04.053
Did you think it'd just get shot down like at the factory

00:46:04.679 --> 00:46:06.514
Or you'd get your idea stolen like today?

00:46:08.224 --> 00:46:10.935
Is that why you didn't say anything when I gave you the chance?

00:46:17.025 --> 00:46:17.984
JEON KEE-TAE KEE-TAE

00:46:20.153 --> 00:46:21.029
Hey.

00:46:23.072 --> 00:46:24.240
I'm on my way.

00:46:38.463 --> 00:46:39.672
It's not that I didn't,

00:46:40.715 --> 00:46:42.300
I just couldn't say it yet.

00:46:43.218 --> 00:46:46.137
Because I'm not completely sure about it right now.

00:47:23.383 --> 00:47:24.509
I'm here.

00:47:24.592 --> 00:47:25.510
Hey.

00:47:27.262 --> 00:47:29.013
This is our team's cash gift for the wedding.

00:47:29.097 --> 00:47:30.056
Pass it along for us.

00:47:30.139 --> 00:47:31.349
Aren't you going?

00:47:31.432 --> 00:47:33.685
I took charge and collected everyone's money,

00:47:33.768 --> 00:47:35.353
But my mother-in-law's coming.

00:47:35.436 --> 00:47:36.396
All right, then.

00:47:36.479 --> 00:47:39.065
I'm going to be there anyway, might as well have a full pocket.

00:47:39.148 --> 00:47:39.983
Thanks.

00:47:41.276 --> 00:47:42.569
Can I just ask one more favor?

00:47:42.652 --> 00:47:43.611
What is it?

00:47:44.195 --> 00:47:47.323
I know you're the Clock-out Fairy, but we need one more person's.

00:47:47.407 --> 00:47:50.159
Dear Fairy, could you stay for a bit and get Mr. Kang's cash gift too?

00:47:50.243 --> 00:47:51.536
No way!

00:47:51.619 --> 00:47:52.954
Mr. Kang makes me uncomfortable.

00:47:53.037 --> 00:47:55.081
Me too, but my mother-in-law is even worse.

00:47:55.164 --> 00:47:57.333
I'm going nuts. I can't. I'm leaving. You're the best!

00:47:57.417 --> 00:47:58.251
Hey!

00:47:58.334 --> 00:47:59.168
Hey!

00:48:00.169 --> 00:48:01.087
Geez.

00:48:04.090 --> 00:48:04.966
JEON KEE-TAE SAEUM

00:48:34.537 --> 00:48:35.830
Why would I go there?

00:48:58.311 --> 00:49:01.147
He snapped at me just for asking if he was going to go.

00:49:03.900 --> 00:49:05.860
So how could I ask him for a cash gift?

00:49:10.782 --> 00:49:12.450
The bus arriving soon

00:49:12.533 --> 00:49:16.204
Is number 266.

00:49:40.728 --> 00:49:43.773
Where did you find this?

00:49:43.856 --> 00:49:45.775
I found it in the product showroom.

00:49:48.611 --> 00:49:49.779
Thank you.

00:49:51.280 --> 00:49:53.449
Did you come all the way here just for this?

00:49:53.533 --> 00:49:55.785
Well, you could say that.

00:49:57.078 --> 00:49:58.496
You could've given it to me later.

00:50:02.500 --> 00:50:03.501
Thank you.

00:50:04.085 --> 00:50:04.919
Well, then

00:50:05.461 --> 00:50:06.504
Have a good night.

00:50:11.134 --> 00:50:12.093
Hello.

00:50:27.358 --> 00:50:29.569
What? Why is he getting on this bus?

00:50:33.948 --> 00:50:35.491
What? No!

00:50:43.708 --> 00:50:45.334
There are plenty of other seats.

00:50:45.835 --> 00:50:47.128
Why sit right next to me?

00:50:48.963 --> 00:50:51.424
Is he following me or something?

00:50:52.133 --> 00:50:52.967
Why?

00:51:00.850 --> 00:51:02.935
I saw a lot of interesting stuff in your notebook.

00:51:05.438 --> 00:51:07.190
Wait, you read my notebook?

00:51:08.107 --> 00:51:09.609
I had to find its owner.

00:51:11.736 --> 00:51:13.529
There were a lot of good ideas in there.

00:51:14.155 --> 00:51:15.323
If it were up to me,

00:51:16.783 --> 00:51:19.327
I'd have given you about ten of those stamps.

00:51:19.410 --> 00:51:20.411
GREAT JOB!

00:51:20.495 --> 00:51:22.205
And one more if that's not enough.

00:51:28.002 --> 00:51:29.796
Thank you?

00:51:31.005 --> 00:51:33.883
Wait, I didn't mean I want one more stamp.

00:51:37.094 --> 00:51:39.889
He came all the way after me to give me my notebook back,

00:51:39.972 --> 00:51:41.724
And now he's complimenting my ideas?

00:51:43.684 --> 00:51:44.644
Could it be?

00:51:48.189 --> 00:51:50.107
I'll make sure it gets delivered safely.

00:51:50.983 --> 00:51:52.568
And what am I supposed to give you?

00:51:52.652 --> 00:51:55.112
Wedding gift money for Ms. Choi Soo-jin.

00:51:55.196 --> 00:51:57.865
Weren't you an engineering major, Ms. Cha?

00:51:58.449 --> 00:52:00.034
That's right, engineering.

00:52:00.117 --> 00:52:02.870
I think you would've been good at something more creative.

00:52:06.999 --> 00:52:08.417
Would you prefer bank transfer?

00:52:08.501 --> 00:52:10.086
Should I give you my bank details?

00:52:10.670 --> 00:52:13.297
Ms. Cha, would you give a cash gift

00:52:13.381 --> 00:52:14.757
For your ex-husband's wedding?

00:52:15.341 --> 00:52:16.467
Sorry?

00:52:17.426 --> 00:52:21.722
This stop is Wonam-dong.

00:52:21.806 --> 00:52:25.601
The next stop is Korea Corporation.

00:52:43.911 --> 00:52:45.496
Mr. Kang is

00:52:46.330 --> 00:52:47.540
Ms. Choi's

00:52:48.207 --> 00:52:49.417
Ex-husband?

00:53:02.513 --> 00:53:04.223
-Ready for the picture? -Come here.

00:53:04.307 --> 00:53:06.267
One, two, three.

00:53:06.976 --> 00:53:08.519
-Let's do one more. -Okay.

00:53:09.186 --> 00:53:10.396
One, two, three.

00:53:11.772 --> 00:53:13.357
-Congratulations. -Stay for the food later.

00:53:13.441 --> 00:53:14.901
There's no way.

00:53:15.526 --> 00:53:17.486
Why would Ms. Choi do that?

00:53:17.570 --> 00:53:19.322
-You look so beautiful! -Thank you.

00:53:19.405 --> 00:53:20.656
Why on earth?

00:53:21.157 --> 00:53:22.450
JULY 26 PARK HYEONG-JIN AND CHOI-SOO JIN

00:53:22.533 --> 00:53:24.368
Don't you think you should go?

00:53:26.120 --> 00:53:27.330
Why would I go there?

00:53:27.413 --> 00:53:30.374
Ms. Cha, would you give a cash gift

00:53:30.458 --> 00:53:31.792
For your ex-husband's wedding?

00:53:48.809 --> 00:53:50.353
This is Cha Ji-yoon.

00:53:50.436 --> 00:53:52.229
I wanted to apologize, Mr. Kang.

00:53:52.313 --> 00:53:54.815
I made a mistake because I didn't know better.

00:53:55.900 --> 00:53:59.028
I'm sorry if I offended you.

00:53:59.862 --> 00:54:03.616
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

00:54:45.241 --> 00:54:49.036
Some people say marriage is where romance goes to die.

00:54:50.246 --> 00:54:51.205
But back then,

00:54:52.123 --> 00:54:53.165
I believed

00:54:55.167 --> 00:54:57.003
That marriage was where romance

00:54:57.086 --> 00:54:58.462
Was made complete.

00:55:07.680 --> 00:55:08.806
HAWAII

00:55:13.060 --> 00:55:14.270
I've made up my mind.

00:55:15.563 --> 00:55:17.648
My honeymoon will be in Hawaii!

00:55:19.650 --> 00:55:21.485
But don't you need to be married to go on a honeymoon?

00:55:21.569 --> 00:55:23.112
Of course.

00:55:27.199 --> 00:55:28.534
Let's just go now.

00:55:28.617 --> 00:55:29.493
What?

00:55:31.120 --> 00:55:34.623
If we go now, plumeria will be in full bloom.

00:55:34.707 --> 00:55:36.375
We can breathe in that scent

00:55:36.459 --> 00:55:38.919
While you swim and I make music.

00:55:39.462 --> 00:55:42.256
What do you think? Doesn't that sound super exciting?

00:55:42.339 --> 00:55:43.299
Yes, it does.

00:55:43.924 --> 00:55:45.801
That's why I'm saving it.

00:55:46.385 --> 00:55:47.553
What?

00:55:47.636 --> 00:55:49.263
-Let's just go. -No.

00:55:49.346 --> 00:55:50.639
-Come on, now. -Stop it.

00:55:50.723 --> 00:55:52.767
-Let's just go! Come on! -Stop it!

00:55:52.850 --> 00:55:54.852
-Let's just go! -Stop that!

00:55:54.935 --> 00:55:56.062
-Let's go! -Stop.

00:55:56.145 --> 00:55:58.022
Huh? Let's go!

00:56:17.917 --> 00:56:20.628
I'm going to see the winter sea. I'll come back with a killer song.

00:56:21.420 --> 00:56:22.296
Love you.

00:56:27.968 --> 00:56:30.930
I loved your free spirit.

00:56:34.517 --> 00:56:38.104
But in the end, that became the reason why we broke up.

00:56:55.329 --> 00:56:56.872
WHY AREN'T YOU HERE?

00:56:56.956 --> 00:56:58.582
WHERE ARE YOU? WHEN ARE YOU COMING BACK?

00:56:58.666 --> 00:57:00.459
I'M WORRIED SO CALL ME PICK UP YOUR PHONE!

00:57:00.543 --> 00:57:03.587
OKAY, LET'S END IT HERE IT'S OVER

00:57:19.061 --> 00:57:21.272
If you're sorry, buy me a drink or something.

00:57:23.691 --> 00:57:26.026
The most important variables in life

00:57:26.652 --> 00:57:27.570
Often appear

00:57:28.362 --> 00:57:30.406
When you least expect them.

00:57:42.126 --> 00:57:43.085
Yes, Mr. Kang.

00:57:43.919 --> 00:57:45.838
-You see me, right? -Sorry?

00:57:46.797 --> 00:57:48.007
Where are you?

00:57:48.090 --> 00:57:49.383
Right across the street.

00:57:54.096 --> 00:57:55.097
Which side?

00:58:19.371 --> 00:58:21.332
You can't just stop there like that.

00:58:29.215 --> 00:58:30.341
Let's go.

00:58:34.470 --> 00:58:35.679
Who would've imagined

00:58:36.263 --> 00:58:39.391
I'd be meeting this guy alone on a weekend?

00:58:40.726 --> 00:58:42.269
Was he always that tall?

00:58:57.451 --> 00:58:59.245
I'm surprised you know a place like this.

00:58:59.828 --> 00:59:01.997
-My friend owns the place. -Welcome to--

00:59:02.081 --> 00:59:04.625
What? When did you get back from the US?

00:59:05.501 --> 00:59:06.919
He gives me free stuff.

00:59:07.503 --> 00:59:09.505
He has a friend?

00:59:09.588 --> 00:59:12.174
If it's this empty, shouldn't you just shut down the place?

00:59:12.258 --> 00:59:14.343
You little punk, first thing you do is nagging?

00:59:14.426 --> 00:59:16.053
Oh, please take a seat here.

00:59:16.136 --> 00:59:17.096
Oh, okay.

00:59:18.764 --> 00:59:20.557
And he's normal.

00:59:28.774 --> 00:59:30.276
Are you okay with single malt?

00:59:30.359 --> 00:59:31.568
Yes, anything is fine.

00:59:33.570 --> 00:59:35.698
What's with this gentle tone?

00:59:43.372 --> 00:59:45.833
Let me run to the storeroom real quick.

00:59:56.760 --> 00:59:59.555
He's like a completely different person outside the office.

01:00:00.806 --> 01:00:02.474
I bet you were surprised to hear from me.

01:00:03.517 --> 01:00:05.311
Yes, a little.

01:00:07.688 --> 01:00:09.106
But why did you

01:00:10.399 --> 01:00:12.026
Did the wedding go well?

01:00:12.860 --> 01:00:15.112
So that's what he wanted to see me for.

01:00:15.195 --> 01:00:16.030
Yes.

01:00:16.613 --> 01:00:17.448
How was it?

01:00:24.330 --> 01:00:26.123
It was normal

01:00:27.791 --> 01:00:28.751
And happy.

01:00:31.420 --> 01:00:32.963
What am I saying?

01:00:38.218 --> 01:00:40.429
The food wasn't great, though.

01:00:45.434 --> 01:00:47.186
What did you do today, Mr. Kang?

01:00:47.853 --> 01:00:49.646
I worked out all day.

01:00:49.730 --> 01:00:50.564
Of course,

01:00:50.647 --> 01:00:53.650
The best thing to do on a day like today is to keep yourself busy

01:00:53.734 --> 01:00:56.653
And drown yourself in alcohol

01:01:00.949 --> 01:01:01.784
Right.

01:01:01.867 --> 01:01:04.453
I guess I should drink quite a bit today.

01:01:16.590 --> 01:01:20.302
I'm no longer the team lead for Product Planning Team 2.

01:01:21.178 --> 01:01:22.221
Pardon?

01:01:23.180 --> 01:01:24.264
I got fired.

01:01:31.021 --> 01:01:33.982
That's exactly why you shouldn't have suggested

01:01:34.066 --> 01:01:37.486
Suspending the whole thing.

01:01:48.914 --> 01:01:49.957
PRESIDENT HAN U-JIN

01:01:51.208 --> 01:01:52.084
It's the President.

01:01:52.543 --> 01:01:53.877
You go on and drink.

01:01:54.503 --> 01:01:56.046
This might take a while.

01:01:56.130 --> 01:01:58.799
Yes. Don't worry about me. Please take your time.

01:02:00.634 --> 01:02:01.468
Mr. Kang!

01:02:03.387 --> 01:02:06.557
Just apologize and beg like you mean it.

01:02:07.099 --> 01:02:08.308
Good luck.

01:02:12.646 --> 01:02:13.856
This is Kang Si-woo.

01:02:16.358 --> 01:02:17.901
He really needs to soften his edges.

01:02:22.114 --> 01:02:23.157
Would you like a refill?

01:02:23.240 --> 01:02:24.116
Please.

01:02:27.953 --> 01:02:29.079
Actually,

01:02:29.163 --> 01:02:30.622
Fill it up.

01:02:30.998 --> 01:02:32.166
All right, fill it up.

01:02:33.250 --> 01:02:34.334
Got it.

01:02:44.136 --> 01:02:48.056
OKAY, LET'S END IT HERE IT'S OVER

01:02:49.391 --> 01:02:50.851
When you think about it,

01:02:52.519 --> 01:02:53.687
I actually

01:02:56.356 --> 01:03:00.319
Got fired by Cho Ga-eul, right?

01:03:05.574 --> 01:03:07.618
I can't even move on to another person like this.

01:03:15.042 --> 01:03:17.586
OKAY, LET'S END IT HERE IT'S OVER DELIVERED

01:03:18.462 --> 01:03:19.296
Yes.

01:03:19.379 --> 01:03:22.466
I'll make sure the handover is completed by next week.

01:03:23.842 --> 01:03:24.676
Okay.

01:03:27.429 --> 01:03:29.681
PRESIDENT HAN U-JIN

01:03:42.277 --> 01:03:43.153
What happened?

01:03:43.237 --> 01:03:45.113
She went crazy as soon as you stepped out.

01:03:46.949 --> 01:03:48.283
I picked the wrong day.

01:03:49.660 --> 01:03:50.953
Come on, get up.

01:03:51.036 --> 01:03:52.162
I'll take you home.

01:03:55.082 --> 01:03:56.208
Excuse me, ma'am?

01:04:01.421 --> 01:04:02.256
What should we do?

01:04:08.679 --> 01:04:09.721
Ms. Cha Ji-yoon.

01:04:09.805 --> 01:04:10.681
Yeah?

01:04:11.890 --> 01:04:12.933
You're late.

01:04:19.231 --> 01:04:22.568
I'm never ever late, you know.

01:04:23.527 --> 01:04:25.153
I may not look it,

01:04:25.237 --> 01:04:27.864
But I'm actually the Clock-in

01:04:27.948 --> 01:04:29.449
And Clock-out fairy.

01:04:31.410 --> 01:04:33.245
A fairy, you say?

01:04:34.580 --> 01:04:36.081
How long have you been a fairy?

01:04:37.916 --> 01:04:40.711
Up until my third year of working,

01:04:41.378 --> 01:04:43.422
I pulled all-nighters like it was nothing.

01:04:43.505 --> 01:04:47.593
I really had so much I wanted to do back then.

01:04:48.510 --> 01:04:51.972
That's when you're full of passion but short on know-how.

01:04:52.055 --> 01:04:53.348
Exactly.

01:04:53.432 --> 01:04:55.976
Then around my fifth year,

01:04:56.560 --> 01:04:58.937
I got so busy handling work dumped down from the higher-ups

01:04:59.021 --> 01:05:00.856
And cleaning up after my subordinates

01:05:00.939 --> 01:05:04.026
That not even ten of me would've been enough.

01:05:04.985 --> 01:05:08.113
Which is also why that's when people switch jobs the most.

01:05:08.196 --> 01:05:11.533
Then one day, I collapsed from burnout.

01:05:13.035 --> 01:05:14.286
Oh, no.

01:05:16.580 --> 01:05:18.332
But nothing happened.

01:05:20.208 --> 01:05:22.669
I took a few sick days,

01:05:23.837 --> 01:05:25.881
But the company kept running just fine.

01:05:28.383 --> 01:05:31.219
I honestly thought it would

01:05:31.303 --> 01:05:34.723
Fall apart if I quit. Seriously.

01:05:34.806 --> 01:05:36.850
But there are always spare parts stacked up

01:05:38.060 --> 01:05:39.019
To replace the broken ones.

01:05:39.603 --> 01:05:40.437
Bingo.

01:05:40.937 --> 01:05:42.272
And so,

01:05:42.356 --> 01:05:45.567
I decided to become a fairy.

01:05:47.986 --> 01:05:49.321
You know, it's like,

01:05:49.821 --> 01:05:52.616
If someone you're hopelessly in love with

01:05:52.699 --> 01:05:55.535
Keeps ignoring your feelings to the end,

01:05:55.619 --> 01:05:59.623
Then you have to put up a wall at some point too.

01:06:00.499 --> 01:06:02.167
So come hell or high water,

01:06:02.250 --> 01:06:04.586
I always leave work when it's time.

01:06:04.670 --> 01:06:08.548
I guess that's my last shred of pride I want to keep intact at work.

01:06:09.341 --> 01:06:12.135
But still, you never ran away.

01:06:14.554 --> 01:06:15.514
Ran away?

01:06:16.932 --> 01:06:17.766
Yeah, that happened.

01:06:22.145 --> 01:06:24.481
I was going to propose, you know.

01:06:25.982 --> 01:06:26.900
But then

01:06:29.236 --> 01:06:30.487
He ran away.

01:06:33.031 --> 01:06:34.074
Who did?

01:06:37.035 --> 01:06:38.286
My boyfriend.

01:06:39.454 --> 01:06:40.580
Wait, no.

01:06:40.664 --> 01:06:41.748
Ex-boyfriend.

01:06:43.291 --> 01:06:44.167
Or, wait.

01:06:44.793 --> 01:06:46.420
Are we not broken up yet?

01:06:47.546 --> 01:06:50.549
No, no. We are broken up.

01:06:50.632 --> 01:06:51.883
Yeah, we broke up.

01:06:52.467 --> 01:06:53.343
So,

01:06:54.136 --> 01:06:56.179
At what point did you start talking about him?

01:06:56.263 --> 01:06:58.724
I mean, it's all the same,

01:06:58.807 --> 01:07:00.684
Dating or working.

01:07:01.184 --> 01:07:05.313
It's all butterflies and excitement at first,

01:07:05.397 --> 01:07:07.858
But after a while, all you see are the flaws.

01:07:09.151 --> 01:07:11.903
But just when you think, "I should quit,"

01:07:11.987 --> 01:07:13.155
Your paycheck comes in,

01:07:13.238 --> 01:07:15.574
And when you think, "I should break up," it's an anniversary.

01:07:16.658 --> 01:07:19.119
Then one day, you have that moment of clarity.

01:07:19.995 --> 01:07:21.705
"What am I doing right now?"

01:07:24.416 --> 01:07:26.042
Yes, I know.

01:07:26.752 --> 01:07:29.463
It's like you said. I'm a coward.

01:07:30.255 --> 01:07:32.716
When something goes wrong, I look for a fallback

01:07:32.799 --> 01:07:34.426
And prepare for a Plan B.

01:07:34.509 --> 01:07:36.762
But how can I help it if that's the best I can do?

01:07:36.845 --> 01:07:38.180
What, are you any different?

01:07:38.263 --> 01:07:40.182
You got fired in the end too!

01:08:01.745 --> 01:08:02.871
Careful.

01:08:03.538 --> 01:08:05.457
At your age, a fall like that can break a bone.

01:08:11.630 --> 01:08:13.632
In this hellish work life,

01:08:14.966 --> 01:08:16.384
Will hope

01:08:17.010 --> 01:08:18.011
Ever show itself?

01:08:23.809 --> 01:08:24.726
Are you free tomorrow?

01:08:26.394 --> 01:08:27.437
Sorry?

01:08:28.939 --> 01:08:29.898
If you are,

01:08:30.899 --> 01:08:32.567
We should meet again.

01:08:41.827 --> 01:08:44.204
Would you be up for another drink

01:08:44.788 --> 01:08:47.249
At my place right now?

01:09:01.054 --> 01:09:04.641
SPECIAL THANKS TO HAN MYEONG-JAE, JUNG MIN-CHUL, O.WHEN

01:09:36.715 --> 01:09:37.966
Ms. Cha,

01:09:38.717 --> 01:09:39.551
I like you.

01:09:40.802 --> 01:09:41.636
Are you insane?

01:09:42.304 --> 01:09:43.138
I'm going to quit!

01:09:43.221 --> 01:09:45.265
You have something with Mr. Kang, right?

01:09:45.765 --> 01:09:47.350
-May I join you? -Take this seat.

01:09:47.434 --> 01:09:48.268
No.

01:09:48.351 --> 01:09:49.728
Then while you're getting caffeinated,

01:09:50.437 --> 01:09:51.646
Shall we have a chat?

01:09:52.814 --> 01:09:54.691
Is this why Mr. Kang asked to see you separately?

01:09:55.692 --> 01:09:57.235
You have feelings for someone?

01:09:58.111 --> 01:09:59.863
You should feel each other out.

01:09:59.946 --> 01:10:01.948
That's why I'd like for us to go

01:10:02.908 --> 01:10:05.327
Butterflies I feel butterflies.

01:10:10.081 --> 01:10:12.083
Subtitle: Yenny Kang

